	(75,1,'2017-12-14 12:40:38','2017-12-14 12:40:38','<strong><em>This is the principal objective of the program “Vietnam Hoteliers – Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam’s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020” launched on June 9<sup>th</sup> in Hanoi.</em></strong>\r\n\r\nThe program is held by Vietnam Hospitality Network, advised and sponsored by Institute for Tourism Development Research.\r\n\r\nVietnam Hospitality Network (VHN) is a non-profit organization, with its operating principle of “Unlimited interaction”, working towards a sustainable future of tourism industry in Vietnam.\r\n\r\nAccording to Mr. Minh Chu - Founder of VHN, the program \"Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system system for Vietnam’s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020\" specifies three main objectives. The first is to create internship opportunities/career opportunities for industry personnel; the second is to efficiently exploit the experts network, connect foreign experts to domestic ones (through interacting on <a href=\"http://hospitality.vn/experts\">http://hospitality.vn/experts</a>- a social page) to enhance sharing, exchanging activities while doing researches on the industry’s issues. The program is expected to involve over 700 hospitality alumni, more than 3000 tourism professionals, more than 1,200 professors and mentors together with over 500 international workers in the industry. The third is to promote networking activities to support the development of human resources and establish businesses cooperation.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-76 size-large\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/941515127698754711-2334550736303955946-nang-cao-1-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"519\" />\r\n\r\nMr. Ha Van Sieu, Head of Institute for Tourism Development Research valued this initiative as an excellent idea, and that this is the solution to an intensive, rapid and substantial improvement of Hotel &amp; Tourism industry’s human resource in the future. He said that high-quality human resource, the leaders, would not only help attract high-end tourists to Vietnam, but also contribute to the success of tourism development, direct it into the right route to professionalism and sustainability, help position Vietnam as a travelling destination.\r\n\r\nCommenting on the program, Mr. Dong Xuan Dam, Dean of Tourism Faculty at National Economics University showed appreciation on how it’d allow and foster knowledge sharing among professors, students and experts in the industry. He pointed out the lack of real life experience, updated knowledge and growing trends in the industry in most of the lectures and lessons taught during classes. Therefore, lectures could be redesigned and improved, students could be exposed to reality, practical trainings in the industry through exchanging news, ideas and expertise knowledge. Besides, this program’d benefit involved parties, schools might be able to help students find employment/internship opportunities, companies would also have the opportunity to find valuable human assets, thereby improving their competitive advantage.\r\n\r\nVHN’s plans for 2014 includes: Free training for 1000 personnel on Online Marketing management for the industry, Workshops for Human Resource Managers, Tourism &amp; Hospitality Management Students gatherings in Switzerland, Hotel managers forum 2014; International Friendship Day event...\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Thảo Linh\r\n</strong></em><em>(Source: http://toquoc.gov.vn/) </em>','Improve the quality of human resource for tourism & hospitality industry','','publish','open','open','','improve-the-quality-of-human-resource-for-tourism-hospitality-industry','','','2017-12-14 13:04:16','2017-12-14 13:04:16','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=75',0,'post','',0),
