	(127,1,'2017-12-14 13:22:19','2017-12-14 13:22:19','<strong><em>On May 3, 2016, Hospitality Talk#1 was held at Hospitality Hub. The event concentrated on the topic: F&amp;B: Service – VIP style and brought about useful information for young talents having passions in Hospitality and Tourism.</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-125\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2033888252058939233-talk1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\nHospitality Talk is a non-profit project which is carried out by the Management Committee of Vietnam Hospitality Network (VHN). As one of the core activities to develop high quality human resources of Tourism and Hospitality in the period of 2015 – 2020, the series of Hospitality Talk will be organized in 10 big cities in Vietnam for all students and young talents who have passion in Tourism and Hospitality. Hospitality Talk aims to provide participants with service-related knowledge and experiences from experts, and then helps them to have be more active and gain more self-confidence through direct interaction with guest speakers.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-121\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/948596188176012280-tallk1a.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\nThe Management Committee of VHN are aware that most of students in this sector now are reluctant to mention their career orientation, as they lack of real life experiences as well as practice environment. Thus, we choose: SERVICE– VIP STYLE as the first Hospitality Talk of 2016’s topic. With new ways of organizing, we attracted many students.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-124\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1725581016637906302-talk1b.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\nOur guest speaker for Hospitality Talk#1 was Ms. Nguyen Ngoc Phuong Thao, the manager of Buffet restaurant, Lobby Lounge, Singapore Lounge of Caravelle, a five-star luxurious hotel placed in the center of Ho Chi Minh city.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-123\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1354158357805210269-talk1d.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\nWith her own experience, Ms. Nguyen enthusiastically shared with the participants necessary skills to become a successful manager in F&amp;B. Moreover, she also helped them to know more about the basic mistakes that we often suffered and ways to overcome them, as well as provided the participants with some tactics to satisfy picky customers.\r\n\r\nMoreover, the participants also had real opportunity to set up western tables and receive guidance of how to gain a 5-star professional service style.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-126\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2041557019899950994-talk1e.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-122\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1074217392718470531-talk1f.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"819\" height=\"460\" />\r\n\r\nThe Hospitality Talk#1 was successful with positive feedbacks from participants. VHN, in general and the Organizing Committee of Hospitality Talk in particular hope that Hospitality Talk with its profound topics will become a meaningful environment for students and experts to sharp their knowledge, gain new experiences, enlarge their relationship and finally create more development and career opportunities for young talents.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AiYpNUYg5uI[/embed]\r\n\r\n<em>Author: Nhu Huynh - Project Coordinator</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Video produced by: Hung Hoang - Project Coordinator</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Translator: B.H.D</em>','Hospitality Talk#1: Service - VIP style','','inherit','closed','closed','','120-revision-v1','','','2017-12-14 13:22:19','2017-12-14 13:22:19','',120,'http://localhost/wordpress/blog/2017/12/14/120-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(128,1,'2017-12-14 13:26:20','2017-12-14 13:26:20','<em><strong>On 2nd, August, 2015, Young Hoteliers Award ended with the exciting and impressive final round after 3 hard-working months of both the Organizing Committee, the candidates and the Jury.</strong></em>\r\n\r\nYoung Hoteliers Award 2015 is a the first contest in Tourism and Hospitality across the country for students living in Vietnam or abroad. The contest aims to find young, enthusiastic and passionate talents who want to develop Tourism and Hospitality industry. The contest has attracted 234 teams from over 30 universities in Vietnam.\r\n\r\nAfter the qualifying round, the TAKE ON BOARD and the SPEED UP round, YHA 2015 has chosen 5 best teams to participate in the final round taken palce in Chacedony Hotel and Movenpick Hotel, Hà Nội.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 days in the final round. The first day includes 2 workshops, aiming to provide the candidates with useful knowledge about Vietnam\'s Tourism and Hospitality:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Part1: Representative of the Organizing Committee - Mr. Pham Hong Chuong - Vice Presidence of National Economics University had a welcoming speech to all candicdates in the contest.</li>\r\n 	<li>Part 2: Workshop \'\' The Development Trend of Tourism and Hospitality\" from representative of BHMS Switzerland- diamond partner and biggest sponsor of Young Hotelier Award 2015.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-129\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/371961338076297976-118004889430298890940777163052964211249842n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Part 3: Workshop \'\' Way to create, manage and develop a successful project\'\' from representative of the jury - Mr. Lương Ngọc Khánh - director of H&amp;K Hospitality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn the officially final part, there are 2 main activities for the 5 best teams: Presentation and Debate.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-130 size-large\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/398563195053341258-117800024585575943131927999797388295248838o-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"585\" />\r\n\r\nIn the presentation, 5 teams have to present, defend their ideas and answer the questions from the jury. The 3 highest - grade teams will continue to join in the Dabate part.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-132\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1422686561981815270-118070994585584609797721763952169388905891o-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"585\" />\r\n\r\nIn the Debate part, each team will have to answer 2 questions from their competitors and at least 1 question from the jury. After 2 rounds, the first prize is belonged to The Playful Chicks with the idea to creat the website <em>yourvietnam.com</em>; which can support travel lovers with neccessary information about places with personal diaries and sharings. The winner will have the chance to visit Switzerland in 7 days and participate in a course of BHMS. There are also other prizes for the 4 other teams.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-133\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1881356051494037050-117798944585587876464067952371404464776680o-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"585\" />\r\n\r\nThe final round ended with happiness. Young Hoteliers Award is now not only a competitive contest, but it is also a place that helps talented people to shine their ideas, make their dreams come true and support for the sustainable development of Tourism and Hospitality of Vietnam.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-131\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/652567394197348165-1181637845855888097973062457353184804137o-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"585\" />\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6wn4ItAYaHY[/embed]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Young Hoteliers Award 2015: Dream comes true','','publish','open','open','','young-hoteliers-award-2015-dream-comes-true','','','2017-12-14 13:32:07','2017-12-14 13:32:07','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=128',0,'post','',0),
