	(193,1,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<em><strong>On April 17th, 2015,  Vietnam Hospitality Network ( VHN) and Ton Duc Thang University together held an event named “ Orientation Day – Seminar for Career Orientation in Tourism and Hospitality”, which attracted more than 1000 students and experts from: WINDFLOWER Boutique Hotel (Mui Ne), Caravelle Hotel ( Sai Gon),...</strong></em>\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-92\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/173910927240790042-11169813101532081198366358115282619183658049n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" />\n\n<em>                    Orientation Day attracted many Tourism and Hospitality Students</em>\n\nFollowing the success of the Orientation Day held in Hanoi on 10th Jan 2015, this is the 2nd event that VHN organized with larger scale and more attractive content. “Orientation” is one of the activities of the program \"Vietnam Hoteliers – Developing the high-quality human resource system for Vietnam’s Tourism and Hospitality\" which is sponsored by the Institute for Tourism Development Research.\n\nWith a \"multi-dimensional interactive platform\" including Nation Tourism Administration Organizations – Manpower – Schools – Experts - Recruiters,  VHN and many tourism universities cross Vietnam expect to help students with their career orientation and want the event to be held annually with larger scale across the country.\n\nAs an activity for students, Orientation Day was not held as the popular workshop with speakers and audiences. This event focused on inspiring students with stories and real experienced shared by the senior managers and experts in this industry. Together with this, Orientation Day also provided an opportunity for students to meet with representatives of the State and recruiters, which would bring them clear and useful knowledge of development of this industry as well as career opportunities.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-93\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/26036553577608647-11146175101532081200716354912994448004567841n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" />  <img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-95\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/626827525375879188-11159487101532081199566357807973642637587431n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"405\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWith significant target and concrete actions, Orientation Day is increasingly getting more support from entities and organizations interested in developing high-quality human resource for supporting the sustainable development Vietnam Tourism and Hospitality.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-94 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/52791225273590693-1106988210153208118286635577757909988516072n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" />\n\n<em>Founder of VHN - Mr. Chu Hong Minh ( in the right) and the Representatives of Ton Duc Thang University gave presents to guest speakers in the end of Orientation Day</em>\n\n<em>For more information, please contact:</em>\n\n<em>Ms. Hanh Bui</em>\n\n<em>Chief Operation Officer - Vietnam Hospitality Network</em>\n\n<em>Email: <a href=\"mailto:hanh.bui@hospitality.vn\">hanh.bui@hospitality.vn</a></em>\n\n<em>Mobile: 093 453 9067</em>','Seminar: Career Orientation in Tourism and Hospitality','','inherit','closed','closed','','91-autosave-v1','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',91,'http://wordpress49.local/blog/2017/12/17/91-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1477,1,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<strong>Vietnam Hospitality Network ( VHN)</strong> is a non-profit project, aiming for the sustainable development of the Tourism and Hospitality industry in Vietnam. VHN operates on \"interactive unlimited\" principle, which concentrates on connecting and maintaining a multi-dimensionally interactive platform (Nation Tourism Administration Organizations – Recruiters – Experts – Manpower- Schools).\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/mNFjfvDLhRI\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Vietnam Hospitality Network','','publish','open','open','','vietnam-hospitality-network-2','','','2017-12-27 19:03:03','2017-12-27 12:03:03','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1477',0,'post','',0),
	(1478,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong><em>This is the principal objective of the program &ldquo;Vietnam Hoteliers &ndash; Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&rdquo; launched on June 9<sup>th</sup> in Hanoi. </em></strong></p>\n\n<p>The program is held by Vietnam Hospitality Network, advised and sponsored by Institute for Tourism Development Research.</p>\n\n<p>Vietnam Hospitality Network (VHN) is a non-profit organization, with its operating principle of &ldquo;Unlimited interaction&rdquo;, working towards a sustainable future of tourism industry in Vietnam.</p>\n\n<p>According to Mr. Minh Chu - Founder of VHN, the program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot; specifies three main objectives. The first is to create internship opportunities/career opportunities for industry personnel; the second is to efficiently exploit the experts network, connect foreign experts to domestic ones (through interacting on <a href=\"http://hospitality.vn/experts\">http://hospitality.vn/experts</a>- a social page) to enhance sharing, exchanging activities while doing researches on the industry&rsquo;s issues. The program is expected to involve over 700 hospitality alumni, more than 3000 tourism professionals, more than 1,200 professors and mentors together with over 500 international workers in the industry. The third is to promote networking activities to support the development of human resources and establish businesses cooperation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/941515127698754711-2334550736303955946-nang-cao-1.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 433px;\" /></p>\n\n<p>Mr. Ha Van Sieu, Head of Institute for Tourism Development Research valued this initiative as an excellent idea, and that this is the solution to an intensive, rapid and substantial improvement of Hotel &amp; Tourism industry&rsquo;s human resource in the future. He said that high-quality human resource, the leaders, would not only help attract high-end tourists to Vietnam, but also contribute to the success of tourism development, direct it into the right route to professionalism and sustainability, help position Vietnam as a travelling destination.</p>\n\n<p>Commenting on the program, Mr. Dong Xuan Dam, Dean of Tourism Faculty at National Economics University showed appreciation on how it&rsquo;d allow and foster knowledge sharing among professors, students and experts in the industry. He pointed out the lack of real life experience, updated knowledge and growing trends in the industry in most of the lectures and lessons taught during classes. Therefore, lectures could be redesigned and improved, students could be exposed to reality, practical trainings in the industry through exchanging news, ideas and expertise knowledge. Besides, this program&rsquo;d benefit involved parties, schools might be able to help students find employment/internship opportunities, companies would also have the opportunity to find valuable human assets, thereby improving their competitive advantage.</p>\n\n<p>VHN&rsquo;s plans for 2014 includes: Free training for 1000 personnel on Online Marketing management for the industry, Workshops for Human Resource Managers, Tourism &amp; Hospitality Management Students gatherings in Switzerland, Hotel managers forum 2014; International Friendship Day event...</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Thảo Linh</strong></em></p>\n\n<p><em>(Source:&nbsp;http://toquoc.gov.vn/)&nbsp;</em></p>\n','Improve the quality of human resource for tourism & hospitality industry','','publish','open','open','','improve-the-quality-of-human-resource-for-tourism-hospitality-industry','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1478',0,'post','',0),
	(1479,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p>\n	(Finance) Institute for Tourism Development Research, Vietnam Hospitality Network in collaboration with Vietstar HBS &ndash; Company of Hotel business solutions, introduced the program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot; in Hanoi. The program has attracted a large number of businesses operating in the tourism sector, universities and experienced professionals in the industry.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n	<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/249466475454825405-vi-su-phat-trien.jpg\" /></p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n	<strong><em>The program &ldquo;Vietnam hoteliers: Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality for the period 201</em></strong><strong><em>5-2020&rdquo; launching ceremony</em></strong><strong><em>. (Source: T.H)</em></strong></p>\n<p>\n	The program works to promote professional networking; help sharpen skills and gain experience; create opportunities to advance career in Hotel &amp; Tourism sector..</p>\n<p>\n	Content activities include:</p>\n<p>\n	First, effectively take advantage of the experts network: connect foreign experts to domestic ones (through http://hospitality.vn/experts) to encourage sharing, exchanging while doing researches on the industry&rsquo;s issues.</p>\n<p>\n	Second, create internship/career opportunities: Sign agreements with enterprises, corporations to support student&rsquo;s researches that are associated with business development, increase internship/ full-time jobs in both quality and quantity.</p>\n<p>\n	Third, better the quality of advanced human resource and promote businesses collaborations: Organize activities to exchange and upgrade management skills as well as business cooperation opportunities such as: Gathering nights of Swiss alumni in hospitality industry, management forum for senior managers, seminars and workshops for HR managers, free training programs for 1,000 personnel on online marketing in hospitality ...</p>\n<p>\n	On the general operation of the VHN, Mr. Ha Van Sieu &ndash; Head of Institue for Tourism Development Research expressed his appreciation for the initiative: &ldquo;I highly appreciate the activities held by the hospitality alumni from Switzerland. The launch of website on hospitality contributes to the intensive, professional and sustainable development of Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism through developing high-quality human resources.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>\n	The VHN generally, and the program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot; in particular promises to capture the attention of the hospitality workers and contribute directly to the industry human resource&rsquo;s quality improvement in the future.</p>','For the sustainable development of Vietnam\'s tourism & hospitality industry','','publish','open','open','','for-the-sustainable-development-of-vietnams-tourism-hospitality-industry','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1479',0,'post','',0),
	(1480,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><em><strong>The requirement that a person working in hospitality industry possess excellent skills in both applying professional knowlege and mastering foreign language is not usually met in tourism human resource in Vietnam.</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>At the press conference of the program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp;&nbsp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot;on June 9th, several solutions and proposals were made. However, it is always easier to talk than to really do.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Collaboration in education</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is forecasted that, by 2020, tourism in Vietnam will have been growing at a continuously positive rate, and have started to change the focus into quality rather than quantity. This means that Vietnam tourism will concentrate on luxury products and services to satisfy the needs of high-end users group who often go on a long holiday. According to calculations, Vietnam will need more than 2.1 million personnel for tourism in 2015 and nearly 3 million in 2020. Current situation in Vietnam can not guarantee those big numbers, as well as can not assure the quality required, therefore, we need help from resources overseas, specifically, education and training collaboration.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/251098160258427599-kho-lap-1.jpg\" style=\"height: 433px; width: 650px;\" /></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Vietnam Hospitality Network (VHN), a non-profit organization working towards a sustainable future of tourism industry in Vietnam, was established to turn ideas into practice. Mr. Minh Chu &ndash; Founder of the VHN told us about 3 main contents: Effectively use of the experts&rsquo; network formed by domestic and foreign experts to exchange ideas, carry out discussions and researches; Connect students with internship/employment opportunities by signing agreements with corporations, organizations; Enhance the interaction among industry senior managers to hone management skills and drive businesses cooperation. VHN also promises to offer free online marketing training to 1000 workers in the industry. According to Mr. Ha Van Sieu, Head of Institute for Tourism Development Research, VHN is the solution of updating trends and knowledge for the human resource we&rsquo;re looking for to fill the skill gap.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Morning at school, afternoon at work</strong></p>\n\n<p>To have qualified associates working in 4-star to 5-star hotels and resorts, one of the proposed solutions was to change education strategy and students&rsquo; internship time. Ms. Phung Thanh Yen &ndash; HR director of Movenpick hotel told us: &ldquo;We need smart students with passion and foreign language fluency. We recommend that students spend at least 3 months doing internship, so that they have enough time to practice and to understand the whole cycle of the business operation.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Moreover, universities should allow flexible school timetable in order for students to work part-time. Students&rsquo; spending more time learning by working and having hands on experience than by staying in classes, taking notes is very popular in foreign countries such as Switzerland, Singapore, France&hellip; Communication and language skills are also improved this way. Approved of this idea, Mr. Dong Xuan Dam &ndash; Dean of Hospitality faculty, National Economics University said that they were negotiating with 4 big hotels to collaborate, but a problem arose that after 8 hours working, students are too exhausted to study. The negotiation then went on to reduce the working time for classes and relaxation but still ensure effectiveness of the working-learning model. Mr.Kai Mercus Schroter &ndash; General Manager of HTM Consultancy company, when talking about the problem, highlighted the importance of communication between Ministry of Education and Training and Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism to make some appropriate changes in internship time. Policy makers should also have real insight into the problem particularly, and into tourism industry in general.</p>\n\n<p><em>Source: Tr&uacute;c Anh -<span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">&nbsp;http://www.ktdt.vn/&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n\n<p><em><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Translator: Thuy Duong</span></em></p>\n','Not easy to bridge the skill gap','','publish','open','open','','not-easy-to-bridge-the-skill-gap','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1480',0,'post','',0),
	(1481,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong><em>As an ambitious young intellectual, Mr. Minh Chu impresses people by his passion and enthusiasm whenever he talks about his tourism &amp; hospitality projects. The Journal of Knowledge and Development had a conversation with him - a young intellectual, founder of Vietnam Hospitality Network, a non-profit organization working towards the sustainable development of Vietnam Tourism.</em></strong></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/3066680129766407829-nguoi-dam-me.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Reporter</strong>:<em> Hello Chu Hong Minh, I know that you graduated with a degree in Finance and Banking, but now you are into tourism development projects. Why did you change?</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Minh Chu</strong>: I love travelling, but I couldn&rsquo;t travel a lot when I was a student. It&rsquo;s not until I went to work did I have the opportunity to travel to many regions in our country. From these trips, with more knowledge, information, understanding accumulated, I came up with many interesting ideas of tourism. It was then like my destiny, because of the passion for tourism, I kept looking around and found my way to study in Switzerland, a country with a thriving tourism industry. I chose hospitality administration, and put all my heart into studying and researching. While studying in Switzerland, I travelled to almost 10 European countries. After finishing the course, I visited some more countries nearby before coming back and working for hotels in Ho Chi Minh City.&nbsp; Then I left for Hanoi, participated intensively in managing development projects for resorts in some of the major tourist attractions of Vietnam. At this time, those trips abroad, along with the practical experience here helped me to discover opportunities and potentials of our tourism industry. I also felt the transformation of the industry in the first decade of the new century and I wished to be a part of the transformation, my desire became to contribute partly to the development of tourism industry.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Reporter:&nbsp;</strong><em>Just as you said that Vietnam tourism shows a significant transformation. What do you think about the opportunity of Vietnam Tourism?</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Minh Chu: </strong>Asia Pacific is a dynamically developing region, Vietnam is included. Our country possesses magnificent beauty of nature, of the country, and the people.&nbsp; Its potential to go ahead is undeniable. After 20 years of innovation, 10 years of implementation of the strategic development of tourism, during the period from 2001 to 2010, Vietnam tourism industry has made significant progress and expected to become one of 10 ideal destinations of the world in the next 10 years. &quot;Vietnam is carrying out regional and international integration. Bilateral, multilateral relations established are more in quantity, broad and intensive in quality on economics, cultural, social, environmental and general issues towards the millennium goals. &nbsp;That context strongly impacts the integration, international cooperation process in tourism. The industry is under the transformation of the decade that moves from developing based mainly on expanding the market, exploiting the available resources, to developing based on manpower, high-quality human resource. Vietnam&rsquo;s receiving the project &ldquo;Responsible Tourism&rdquo; funded by EU, and the coming implementation of ASEAN mutual recognition arrangement on tourism professionals are opportunities, and at the same time, challenges for Vietnam tourism.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Reporter:</strong><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong>As the founder of VHN, with the purpose of developing tourism industry sustainably, what is the focus of its program, after nearly six years operating?</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Minh Chu: </strong>Vietnam Hospitality Network - www.hospitality.vn started in 2008 by a group of hotel management graduated students from Switzerland. With the valuable experience we gained when studying and working in developed countries of hospitality industry and our desire to contribute to the sustainable development of Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry, we all together established VHN. Our perspective is that for the development to be sustainable, the participants (manpower, schools, experts, recruiters and tourism administration organizations) have to connect closely with each other. And here we create a multidimensional interactive platform, where every member can maximize their benefits by building up professional relationships, improving operational skills and experience, developing career opportunities and business opportunities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Reporter:</strong><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong>I know that you are supported by the Institute for Tourism Development Research in developing high-quality human resource for the industry in the period of 2015-2020, can you share some information about this?</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Minh Chu:</strong>Yes, we are working with the Institute for Tourism Development Research to develop high-quality human system for the period of 2015-2020. We are sponsored and supported greatly by the Institute in operating the project with three main objectives:</p>\n\n<p>- Efficiently take advantage of the experts network, connect foreign experts to domestic ones (through interacting on <a href=\"http://hospitality.vn/experts\">http://hospitality.vn/experts</a>- a social page)</p>\n\n<p>- Create internship opportunities/career opportunities for industry personnel, sign agreements with corporates, business, administration agencies&hellip; to support and create opportunities for them.</p>\n\n<p>-Organize activities to exchange and upgrade management skills as well as business cooperation opportunities such as: Swiss Alumni Nights, management forum for senior managers, seminars and workshops for HR managers, free training programs for 1,000 personnel on online marketing in hospitality &hellip;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Besides, we also know that with the development of Vietnam tourism in the new period, human resource currently can&rsquo;t satisfy the needs in quantity and quality, we seriously lack the high-quality resource. However, the good news is that there are many hospitality management graduated students from developed countries, especially from Switzerland. Some of them didn&rsquo;t have enough experience, some of them couldn&rsquo;t handle the differences in working here from working in foreign countries, those facts limited them from developing their careers further. Therefore, our projects focus on Vietnamese students graduated from developed countries in general, and from Switzerland particularly (The Swiss Alumni Club) as the main resource, to assist them, equip them with substantial knowledge and skills to take management positions within 3-5 years after coming back.</p>\n\n<p>With these objectives, we hope that the program will practically meet the industry requirements, and can contribute greatly to the development of the industry.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Reporter:&nbsp;</strong><em>Thank you, Minh for the conversation today and we wish you success in the future!</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Source: Knowledge &amp; Development</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Translator: Thuy Duong</em></p>\n','A passion for tourism','','publish','open','open','','a-passion-for-tourism','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1481',0,'post','',0),
	(1482,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><em><strong>In June 9, 2014, the conference announced the program &quot;Developing the high quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s Tourism and Hospitality for the period 2015- 2020&quot; took place at the Movenpick Hotel Hanoi with the participation of the Institute for Tourism Development Research, Vietnam Hospitality Network, businesses, universities and experts in Tourism and Hospitality industry.</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Vietnam Hospitality Network ( VHN) is a non-profit project, aiming for the sustainable development of the Tourism and Hospitality industry in Vietnam. VHN operates on &quot;interactive unlimited&quot; principle, which concentrates on connecting and maintaining a multi-dimensionally interactive platform (Nation Tourism Administration Organizations &ndash; Recruiters &ndash; Experts &ndash; Manpower- Schools). From here, each member can optimize benefits include: building professional relationships, skills and experience, finding career development opportunities and doing business.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/496218338469795131-hop-bao.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>Realizing VHN is a new and potential idea that can support for the development of hospitality advanced human resources, the Institute for Tourism Development Research has supported the project enthusiastically and become a special adviser unit and the main sponsor for the program &quot;Developing the high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s Tourism and Hospitality for the period 2015 - 2020&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>Speaking at the press conference, Dr. Ha Van Sieu &ndash;the Presidence of Institute for Tourism Development Research said that: According to the forecast of the Vietnam tourism development strategy and the Master Plan for Vietnam tourism development from 2020 to 2030, Vietnam will have a serious lack of human resource, particularly in human quality. The reason is that the supply of students from tourism and hospitality universities cannot meet with with the strong development of Vietnam tourism in both quantity and quality. Dr. Ha Van Sieu also emphasized that in tourism and hospitality, human resource plays a decisive role. Thus, we need to improve the quality of human resource in order to enhance the hospitality value. Meanwhile, that we change the quality of human industry through developing the quality of training facilities will take lots of time. Hence, the appearance of VHN which focuses on multi-dimensional interaction of many groups objects is a new ray of hope for the hospitality and tourism human resource development.</p>\n\n<p>Dr. Ha Van Sieu also appreciated the participation of Switzerland international students in the VHN. He believed that with the activities and contributions of this network, the hospitality human resource will soon meet the requirements of Vietnam tourism: development in depth, quality, professionalism and sustainability.</p>\n','Press Conference “Developing the high quality human resource system in Vietnam’s Tourism and Hospitality for the period 2015 – 2020”  ','','publish','open','open','','press-conference-developing-the-high-quality-human-resource-system-in-vietnams-tourism-and-hospitality-for-the-period-2015-2020-','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1482',0,'post','',0),
	(1483,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><em><strong>In 31<sup>st</sup> August, 2013, at Hilton Hanoi Opera, Switzerland International Students Alumni held the program Swiss Alumni Night.</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Following the success of the program in 2012 in Saigon, this year, the event was held in Hanoi with the purpose of connecting international student community, creating business opportunities, supporting each other in their work and especially orienting for international students studying tourism and hospitality in Switzerland, as well as conveying the experiences for any students who planned to Switzerland in the future.</p>\n\n<p>The program attracted nearly 100 participants including former international students, new international students and guests who were coming from the state, corporations or companies whose work related especially to personnel and networking.</p>\n\n<p>The event was started from 20:30 but participants came very early to have time to talk, exchange and get acquainted with each other.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1578704057521674853-san1.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">After spending a few times for experts to share about their experiences in hotel management, the music began.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2383756101756258648-san2.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;The Connecting Gameshow is the part that people expected the most. This was the opportunity to participate in the event,understand each other better, make connections and build teamwork.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/570627879216383632-san3.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>As a Vietnamese student who had studied hotel management and tourism in Switzerland, Ms. Nguyen Hai Anh (currently working for Vietnam Airlines magazine) said:&nbsp;<em> I have an unforgettable time studying in Switzerland. And tonight, it is really great to see my friends again and call back all the memories when I was in dorm. I have found that time is precious and gives me much knowledge about my major.</em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/378504129988166671-san4.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>The Vietnamese students in Switzerland has been training and practicing in one of the most professional hospitality and tourism environments in the world. &nbsp;Here is the chance to connect all international students together in order to create more job opportunities for me as well as all of you.</em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/400189635511944628-san5.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mr.Tran Duc Viet, who is currently a final year student of an university of hotel and tourism in Lausanne now is an internship at a famous hotel corporation in Vietnam said that: <em>Taking part in this event, I want to meet other Vietnamese students who had studied in Switzerland and ask them some questions about their experiences or advice of some high quality and potential graduate schools. In addition, this is also my opportunity to meet other international students and create a community that can help each other in school and in future careers after we complete the MBA in Hospitality and Tourism in Switzerland.</em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mr. Ta Minh Thao, representative of the Organizing Committee said:<em> When coming back to Vietnam, we realized that we needed an organization to connect all students with companies related to Hospitality and Tourism and the state administration together.</em></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/619155264695250923-san6.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>Therefore, the social networking Hospitality.vn was born as a bridge to support Vietnamese students, provide an advanced human resource for Tourism and Hospitality as well as orient for students who want to study at Switzerland. Swiss Alumni Events is a chance for students to connect and hopes to receive more attention from Vietnamese students who study in Switzerland to help the Switzerland Alumni Vietnam Association grow more prosperously.</p>\n\n<p><em>Source: John Ta - Alumni from Switzerland</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Translator: B.H.D</em></p>\n','Swiss Alumni Night 2013 - Connecting Switzerland international students community','','publish','open','open','','swiss-alumni-night-2013-connecting-switzerland-international-students-community','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1483',0,'post','',0),
	(1484,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><em><strong>Beside knowledge and experience, soft skills are critically important to success. Courses on soft skills, business communication are opened and grabbed the attention of a large part of white-collar workers, businessmen, middle and senior managers...</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>A very popular unanswered question in today&rsquo;s workplace is that among many essential soft skills, what the most needed skill is, which skill needs to be mastered the most in order to optimize efficiency at work and even in everyday life. In one survey of CEOs done by Fortune 500, it shows that Networking is the most important skill, accounting for 75% success in professional work. This is not a subjective judgment, it is the result of the actual research and it has scientific basis. Networking is not just participating in an event or meeting a group of people. Networking skill is the ability to find, build and connect the relationships and resources to create and develop new opportunities. Therefore, in business, Networking skills are particularly important, especially to the leaders, because the success of their business not only depends on their knowledge and skills, but on the knowledge and skills of their whole network.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/47919455740361359-noi-gap-go.png\" /></p>\n\n<p>Networking is not a new concept in Western countries. But in Vietnam, networking has just been focused and mentioned for the last few years. People have taken networking more serious, more conscious, more proactive, planned and focused more on the quality of the relationship. And along with that trend, networking in tourism &amp; hospitality industry increasingly reflects its role in determining the success of an individual as well as the prosperity of a business. In a multidimensional playground like tourism &amp; hospitality, networking becomes an art, it becomes vital rather than merely a needed soft skill.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1978862179975606208-noi-gap-go1.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>Being aware of the importance of networking in the industy, management team of Vietnam Hospitality Network (hospitality.vn, abbreviated VHN), from the early days, identified one of the key objectives is to connect, maintain and gather strength of high-quality human resource community. From the experience and achievements through the operating and developing, VHN wants to be the bridge between professional groups in the industry through online and offline events, from which each and everyone can get real benefits from building professional relationships and developing career opportunities. And to improve the quality of networking activities, to make networking a professional activity and create viral effect, we organized Hospitality Gathering &ndash; A networking event where senior personnel in the industry met in major cities across Vietnam. With an effort to connect and inspire people, last year, Hospitality Gathering events were held in Hanoi, Saigon, Vung Tau, Da Nang, Nha Trang,... and became a trademark of VHN, where tourism &amp; hospitality enthusiasts met.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/286356029444764029-noi-gap-go2.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>To make it a playground for high-quality human resource of the industry, we invited participants for Hospitality Gathering events selectively, our management team focused tremendously on quality and effective networking. In each Gathering event, we have special guests which can be the senior managers, individuals taking important positions in large enterprises. Besides the success career storytelling, experiences sharing, Hospitality Gathering promotes business cooperation - this is the true &quot;value&quot; that VHN gives to participants.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/1196983569040066292-noi-gap-go4.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>With the intention of promoting conscious networking activities in human resource of the industry, through dozens of Hospitality Gathering events, our management team has been greatly encouraged by the success of the relationships developed at the events. And certainly, Hospitality Gathering will keep spreading and connecting people in the future.</p>\n\n<p><em style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Hanh Bui &ndash; VHN Chief Operating Office</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Translator: Thuy Duong</em></p>\n','Hospitality Gathering – where tourism passions meet','','publish','open','open','','hospitality-gathering-where-tourism-passions-meet','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1484',0,'post','',0),
	(1485,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong><em>The program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; &nbsp;hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot; was officially announced on June 9 in Hanoi with the participation of representatives from Institute for Tourism Development Research, Vietnam Hospitality Network, as well as corporations operating in the tourism sector, universities and experienced professionals in the industry.</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Vietnam Hospitality Network, hereinafter referred to as the VHN, is a non-profit organization working towards the sustainable development of the hospitality industry in Vietnam. VHN operates on the principle of &quot;Unlimited interaction&quot;; undertakes the mission to create and maintain a multi-dimensional platform where 5 interdependent factors of human resource: Manpower - Schools &ndash; Recruiters &ndash; National Tourism Administration organizations communicate and influence each other. In that multi-dimensional interactive environment, individuals can optimize benefits from building professional relationships; gaining skills &amp; experience; taking opportunities to advance career or develop their own business.</p>\n\n<p>With that mission, VHN receives support and assistance from businesses, schools, partners, National Tourism Administration organizations, especially our advisor &ndash; sponsor, Institute for Tourism Development Research.</p>\n\n<p>The program includes many activities with diversified content, all following three main directions:</p>\n\n<p>The first is to effectively take advantage of the network of experts; connect foreign experts to domestic ones to encourage sharing, exchanging in researches on the industry&rsquo;s issues.</p>\n\n<p>The second is to increase career opportunities by quantity and quality for the industry workforce, for example, by creating internships for students through agreements with corporations, organizations to support them in projects/researches that are associated with business development.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2530789900846827769-about.jpg\" style=\"height: 433px; width: 650px;\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4;\"><em>The participants exchanged views on issues of human resource development in hospitality industry at the conference</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>The final one is to organize activities aiming at improving management quality of the leaders - advanced human resource and promoting business collaboration opportunities such as a management forum for senior managers, seminars, workshops for HR managers, free training programs for 1,000 associates on online marketing in hospitality industry&hellip;</p>\n\n<p>On the general operation of the VHN, Mr. Ha Van Sieu &ndash; Head of Institue for Tourism Development Research expressed his appreciation for the initiative: &ldquo;I highly appreciate the activities held by the hospitality alumni from Switzerland. The launch of website on hospitality contributes to the intensive, professional and sustainable development of Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism through developing high-quality human resources&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p>The VHN generally, and the program &quot;Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam&rsquo;s tourism &amp; hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020&quot; in particular promises to capture the attention of the hospitality workers and contribute directly to the industry human resource&rsquo;s quality improvement in the future.</p>\n\n<p><em>Source: Th&uacute;y Hương -<span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">&nbsp;http://tuoitrethudo.vn/&nbsp;</span></em></p>\n\n<p><em><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Translator: B.H.D</span></em></p>\n','Announcement of the program \"Vietnam Hoteliers - Developing high-quality human resource system for Vietnam’s tourism &  hospitality industry for the period 2015-2020”','','publish','open','open','','announcement-of-the-program-vietnam-hoteliers-developing-high-quality-human-resource-system-for-vietnams-tourism-hospitality-industry-for-the-period-2015-2020','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1485',0,'post','',0),
	(1486,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong><em>With a desire to develop a new generation of leaders for Service in Vietnam which is neccessary for domestic demand and also provides high quality human resources, Vingroup creates a Scholarship Fund &quot;Capacity development for enterprise managers in Vietnam&rdquo;. In&nbsp; the 1st step, Vingroup sponsored 10 million dollars, equivalent to 220 billion VND. In January, 2015, the Fund will launch the first project of traning high quality human resource, specialized in Tourism and Hospitality. </em></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><em><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2357981135560136302-vinpearl-premium-da-nang-1.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 279px;\" /></em></strong></p>\n\n<p>The Scholarship Fund &quot;Capacity development for enterprise managers in Vietnam&quot; set a goal for creating and training a young, educated, skillful (based on international standard) generation of CEO and managers, provides them enough knowledge to manage and operate the high quality facilities in Vietnam, especially in specific areas such as hotels, resorts, commercial centers (shopping center), and other business and service establishments.</p>\n\n<p>In order to achieve this goal, Vingroup doesn&rsquo;t only create the Scholarship Fund &quot;Capacity development for enterprise managers in Vietnam&quot; but also directly participates in operating the specialized training programs, together with experienced organizations which are famous for developing practical management capabilities for services industry.</p>\n\n<p>By making drastic, effective and practical plan, the Fund will provide a practical training environment, concentrate on connecting 4 core aspects of leadership development: internationally professional standards; international training programs; advanced environmental practices and employment opportunities, immediately after training. This approach provides an open future for the young leader.</p>\n\n<p>From 1/2015, the Fund will run the first project: recruiting and training in order to find 50 Vietnamese General Manager (GM) for five-star hotels and resorts. Currently, most of the GM are&nbsp; foreigners, because the human resources of Vietnam do not meet the specific requirements of the field.</p>\n\n<p>The project will be implemented in 12 months, for the Vietnamese potential candidates, from 25 to 35, who have energy, passion and desire to develop a career in hotel management. The successful candidates will be trained by the famous and international organization such as American Hotel &amp; Lodging Educational Institute ( AHLEI). The Certified Hotel Administrator ( CHA) of AHLEI is the most prestigious certification for the manager and the hotel manager, which is recognized worldwide. Candidates will also have chances to practice in the network of five-star hotels and resorts in Vietnam. Graduate candidates will be certified and confirmed by AHLEI and have internship certification from Vingroup. In particular, the best candidates will continue to receive scholarships to practice 2 weeks in Singapore, Dubai, Switzerland; also be considered simultaneously by Vingroup to be appointed to GM position immediately after completing the program.</p>\n\n<p>Vingroup have scholarships available from 50% to 100% of tuition for qualified candidates. During the training period, trainees will be paid accordingly.</p>\n\n<p><em>Source: Vingroup</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Translator: B.H.D</em></p>\n','Vingroup creates the 10 – million dollars Scholarship Fund: \"Capacity development for enterprise managers in Vietnam\"','','publish','open','open','','vingroup-creates-the-10-million-dollars-scholarship-fund-capacity-development-for-enterprise-managers-in-vietnam','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1486',0,'post','',0),
	(1487,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong>PART 1: DEVELOPMENT PLAN INTRODUCTION</strong><br />\n<br />\nWith the mission to develop young talented leaders for Vietnam service sector, Vingroup corporation established a scholarship fund named &ldquo;Developing capacity of Vietnamese corporate managers&rdquo; in January 2015.</p>\n\n<p>Elite hospitality group, in collaboration with Vingroup, launched the project &ldquo;Hotel managers training&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p>Local tourism administration organizations and agencies jointly hold the events (as described below), to enhance the cooperation among government, entrepreneurs and educators in adopting the strategy to develop high-quality human resources for Vietnam.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/131039868113677938-10940573101530237044216357875231939995847173n.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 461px;\" /></p>\n\n<p>Planned agenda:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Representatives of local Tourism Administration agencies/organizations to deliver speech of Tourism development strategy</li>\n	<li>Introduction of Scholarship Fund</li>\n	<li>Introduction of the training program</li>\n	<li>&ldquo;Commucation skills for managers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Schedule:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Time: 8.00am &ndash; 9.30am on Saturday, January 31<sup>st</sup>, 2015</li>\n	<li>Venue: Vinhomes Riverside &ndash; No.7 Bang Lang 1 Strt, Long Bien Dist., Hanoi</li>\n	<li>Organizer: Elite Hospitality Group</li>\n	<li>Partner: Vietnam Hospitality Network &ndash; VHN (<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fhospitality.vn%2F&amp;h=YAQFzFpqg&amp;enc=AZMh3B5bndgusUQIdgId_6krG-TLgW-iA8ajyxvYx9cwtkDiLYRNkiQSZjID970l-Xc&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\">http://hospitality.vn/</a>)</li>\n	<li>Content: Elite Hospitality Group</li>\n	<li>Sponsor: Vingroup</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Participants:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Representatives of Tourism Administration Organizations</li>\n	<li>Representativesof VGR</li>\n	<li>Representatives of Elite</li>\n	<li>Attendees who concern</li>\n	<li>Reporters<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><em>Registration deadline: January 28<sup>th</sup>, 2015.</em></strong><br />\n<strong><em><strong>Please send your CV to:</strong><br />\n<strong>(Ms.) Hạnh</strong></em></strong> <strong><em>B&ugrave;i -&nbsp;Project Manager - Vietnam Hospitality Network</em></strong><br />\n<strong><em><strong>Tel: 093 453 9067/&nbsp;Email: </strong></em></strong><a href=\"mailto:hanh.bui@hospitality.vn\"><em>hanh.bui@hospitality.vn</em></a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/363542992220636803-inforumhn-page-001.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 375px;\" /></em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>PART II: &ldquo;EFFECTIVE COMMUNICATION SKILLS&rdquo;</strong></p>\n\n<p><br />\nAlong with the Seminar &ldquo;Strategy of developing Vietnamese talents for hospitality industry&rdquo;&rdquo;, Vingroup funded a training program named &quot;Effective Communication Skills&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>- Please send your CV to this email address: hanh.bui@hospitality.vn<br />\n- Registration deadline: January 28<sup>th</sup>, 2015</p>\n\n<p>- Targeted participants:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Age: 25-35&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Have a bachelor degree&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>English language requirements: IELTS 4.0 or TOEIC 401 or TOEFL iBT 41&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Have 3 to 5 years of experience in service sector&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Middle to upper managers (at least 2 years of experience in management positions)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Have a desire to improve and master communication skills&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Not recommended for those who don&rsquo;t have enough experience in the field and in management positions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">BENEFITS</strong></p>\n\n<p>- Internationally standardized curriculum from American Hotel and Lodging Educational Institute</p>\n\n<p>- Build up relationships and exchange knowledge</p>\n\n<p>- Improve personal competitive advantage in advancing career</p>\n\n<p>- Improve self-confidence and flexibility in any situation.</p>\n\n<p>- Unlock self-potential and develop charisma to partners.</p>\n\n<p>- Improve personal brand image</p>\n\n<p>- Discover the key to success and advancement in career</p>\n\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">PURPOSE</strong></p>\n\n<p>- Practice the use of body language to make a positive impact when communicating</p>\n\n<p>- Practice listening skills and effective questions making when communicating.</p>\n\n<p>- Practice attentive listening skills to understand messages during conversations transmitted through body language.</p>\n\n<p>- Learn how to strike up a conversation, create impressions along with attraction, persuasion through the steps to control and lead the conversations.</p>\n\n<p>- Recognize the role of non-verbal communication</p>\n\n<p>- Find solutions to overcome barriers in communication.</p>\n\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">CONTENT</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">- Evaluation of the effectiveness in communication</span></p>\n\n<p>- Hypothesis of communication skills</p>\n\n<p>- Challenges in communication</p>\n\n<p>- The art of public speaking</p>\n\n<p>- Elements of communication</p>\n\n<p>- The art of nonverbal communication</p>\n\n<p>- Tone and intonation management skills in communication</p>\n\n<p>- The art of listening</p>\n\n<p>- Application of communication tools</p>\n\n<p>- Phone communication</p>\n\n<p>- Use of technology in communication</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em>Translator: Th&ugrave;y Dương</em></p>\n','Seminar: Strategy of developing Vietnamese talents for hospitality industry','','publish','open','open','','seminar-strategy-of-developing-vietnamese-talents-for-hospitality-industry','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1487',0,'post','',0),
	(1488,0,'2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','<p><strong><em>With an increasing by 10% of international visitors each year, together with the development of domestic tourism, Vietnam tourism in recent years has made a significant contribution to the economic and social development. However, the development of tourism and hospitality human resources is not directly proportional to the growth of the tourism industry. Thus, the tourism industry has now been craving for people who are experienced and dedicated to their career.</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Lacking and weak</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Besides popular visitors, people who come from Russia, South Korea, Japan, Germany, Spain travelling to Vietnam are increasing. However, due to lack of training qualified staffs, Vietnam tourism does not have enough tour guides.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/2498999930355218443-nhanluc1.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 478px;\" /></span></p>\n\n<p><em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Training staffs in luxury hotels</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Currently, there are over 6,700 tour guides for international visitors, including about 3,700 tour guides speaking English (equivalent to nearly 50%), nearly 1,000 guides speaking French, 961 guides speaking Chinese, etc. Meanwhile, Vietnam tourism in 2015 aims to welcome more than 1 million Japanese tourists and the number of Japanese tour guide will be 3-time increase compared with today. However, this is hardly feasible because in 1&nbsp; to 2 years, Vietnamese tour guides can not be trained to speak fluently Japanese.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Due to the growing demand of tourists, while we do not have enough tour guides, many units have to hire people who once exported to foreign countries and train them as tour guides. Problem here is they are good at language but &quot;empty&quot; of professional knowledge which will negatively affect the tour quality. Recently, the &ldquo;illegal&rdquo; situation has appeared, while more tourist guides are foreigners, mainly in the South Korean, Japan, Russia. They are mostly staffs from foreign travel companies who go with the tourists to Vietnam, set a tour, book hotels, etc and do the role of tour guides as well. This situation does not only cause revenue loss and make it difficult to control the service quality, but also negatively affect the image and reputation of Vietnam tourism.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/3297450721388131002-daotaonhanluc1.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 488px;\" /></p>\n\n<p><em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Communication traning in luxury hotels</em></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Vietnam hospitality industry also face the same issue; we do not have qualified and skillful human resources. Meanwhile, there are currently more than 14,200 accommodation establishments with 320,000 rooms for tourists, specially rooms at 3 to 5 &ndash; star hotel are more than 34%. Human Resource Management Representative at Hilton hotel said: &quot;The weakness of Vietnam is the lack of personnel skills, thus staffs should often be retrained. Not only the language but also the servicing skills can&rsquo;t reach international standards &quot;.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">Trinh Xuan Dung, former president of Hanoi Tourism College said: &quot;Most of the students studying tourism and hospitality are taught with academic knowledge, which is only suitable for research activities. Due to lack of practice, most tourism and hospitality students must attend extra classes and learn more soft skills. Meanwhile, in foreign countries, sophomores have the chance to do the internship in restaurants and hotels to get real experiences.&quot;</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Need radical solution</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Mr. Mai Tien Dung, deputy director of the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism (MOCST) said that if the number of visitors increases, rather we have to catch the opportunity, but the reality is somewhat passive, we adapt quite slow to the market&rsquo;s change.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://wordpress49.local/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/145027872932701492-daotaonhanluc2.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 530px;\" /></p>\n\n<p><em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Students are trained cooking in hotels</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>He also said: The increasing tourists from Russia, South Korea, Japan is really good, but we are unable to catch up with the growth speed because we do not have enough qualified tour guides. As a rule, people who want to become&nbsp; tour guides for international tourists need to graduate from universities, have good language, expertise, health ... However, in fact, Vietnam do not have lots of advanced staffs as expected. That makes balancing the supply &ndash; demand more difficult.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>To deal with this situation, according to Mr.Nguyen Cong Hoan, deputy director of Hanoi Redtour, some travel agencies have been reluctant to find solutions such as using international tour guides and having some people to translate what the guides said into the language of visitors. This affects the quality of information given to the tourists.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">In general, these solutions are just temporary, we should soon have more radical plans in order to deal with market changes as well as joint training between enterprises and schools. &quot;Recently, a number of joint training activities between enterprises and schools has worked quite effectively. However, this activity still works alone. Consequently, we need support from nation tourism organizations, specially from the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism. In fact, the lack of tour guides and hotel staffs has occurred more than 10 years and has been forecasted a lot, but so far there is no solution&quot;, a leader of Vietnam Tourism Association recommended .</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Experts have warned that if there is no strategy and training plan, the quality of tourism human resource in our country will soon be lower. Currently, approximately 70 institutions just train about 13,000 students each year, which only meet 55% of the demand. According to the Institute for Tourism and Development Research, up to 2015, the tourism industry will need 620,000 direct employees in total 2.2 million created jobs and by 2020 this figure will amount to 870,000 people.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Mr. Nguyen Manh Cuong, Deputy Director of Vietnam National Administration of Tourism, said that in the near future, the tourism industry will work with enterprises and &nbsp;schools to find solutions to train tour guides with neccesary languages.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Xu&acirc;n Minh</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">(baotintuc.vn)</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','Tourism lacks of qualified human resources','','publish','open','open','','tourism-lacks-of-qualified-human-resources','','','2017-12-17 07:26:02','2017-12-17 07:26:02','',0,'http://wordpress49.local/?p=1488',0,'post','',0);
